data: {"type":"response.function_call_arguments.done","arguments":"{\"title\":\"Weather Patterns in California\",\"content\":\"### California Climate Zones\\nCalifornia is known for its diverse climate zones, which include:\\n\\n- **Coastal Climate**: Mild, wet winters and dry summers. Influenced by the Pacific Ocean, leading to moderate temperatures.\\n- **Desert Climate**: Found in southeastern California, characterized by hot summers and mild winters with minimal rainfall.\\n- **Mountain Climate**: Higher elevations experience colder temperatures and more precipitation, often in the form of snow.\\n- **Central Valley Climate**: Hot, dry summers and cool, wet winters. This area is a major agricultural hub due to its fertile soil.\\n\\n### Seasonal Weather Variations\\nCalifornia experiences distinct seasonal variations:\\n\\n- **Winter**: Generally mild in coastal areas but can be cold and snowy in the mountains. Rainfall is more common during this season.\\n- **Spring**: Transitional period with warming temperatures and decreasing rainfall.\\n- **Summer**: Hot and dry, especially inland. Coastal areas remain cooler due to ocean breezes.\\n- **Fall**: Gradual cooling with the onset of the rainy season in late fall.\"}","item_id":"fc_0f143347523ad8f50069bb43855910819b96872e5cabce021f","output_index":1,"sequence_number":492}

